HEADWORD: Pectolite
<hw>Pec"to*lite</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧k"t⟦osl⟧*l⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>pecten</ets> a comb + <ets>-lite</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A whitish mineral occurring in radiated or
fibrous crystalline masses. It is a hydrous silicate of lime and
soda.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

